  "name": "Morrison CFD Hemolysis — CPB Credibility Package (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This unit of assurance documents the credibility evidence for a CFD-based hemolysis prediction model applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass operating conditions. The model has been applied in clinical research contexts to support identification of worst-case hemolysis operating points for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. A 13-factor credibility assessment was conducted per ASME V&V 40-2018, with 7 factors formally assessed and 6 scoped out as acceptable at MRL 2. All assessed factors meet or exceed their required credibility levels. This package conforms to the Minimal profile; full structured use-scope metadata is not encoded in a ContextOfUse object.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-worst-case",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-generic-cbp-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-cbp-experimental-hemolysis-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-cfd-validation-runs-2023"
  ],
